# FUTURE — nice-to-have follow-ups (project shell)

- Dark mode activation (whole-app slice, new behavior → design-lead/tech-lead):
  the 墨 night-study ladder is designed and recorded in
  packages/design-tokens/src/ink-jade.css (header comment) — page stays lit,
  walls double their whisper, actives lighten, inks flip. Needs a theme toggle
  + `.dark` overrides for the FULL token set (cards, borders, review tints),
  not just the shell ladder.
- PaneHeader chip seating unification: the centered chat title chip
  (features/chat/ThreadSwitcherPopover.tsx, variant="tab") sizes itself
  `h-9` against the h-10 band because PaneHeader centers its title slot;
  ContextTabBar seats chips via items-stretch instead. The stronger move is
  one adaptive band-chip geometry (PaneHeader items-stretch + grammar-owned
  fit) so no consumer knows the band height. Reviewer-endorsed, low urgency
  while both values are stable.
- Chats as a working-set tab strip (user floated 2026-07-15): multiple chat
  tabs + "+" in the centered chat band, like document tabs. Needs an
  "open chats" model (close ≠ delete, overflow, ordering) and resolves how
  chat navigation relates to the sidebar → design-lead/tech-lead. The
  single-title tab chip shipped in slice 7 is the compatible first step.
- Clay secondary (palette proposal, not adopted): a cinnabar-family secondary
  surface (~oklch(0.92 0.012 29)) if secondary chips ever need to leave the
  page-neutral ladder.
- Future pin/favorite mark: red is now spent on the shelf surface — a pin mark
  cannot rely on cinnabar alone if the rail ever warms toward red; use shape/weight or
  the reserved gold voice.
- DockViewSwitch ARIA: the contained segmented switch still uses
  role="tablist"/"tab" markup (dock/DockHeader.tsx). Decide whether tabs
  semantics (views of one surface) or a radiogroup/toggle-group better
  matches the interaction, and align keyboard behavior with the choice.
- Invalid explicit `?thread=` id: useResolvedChatThread trusts the route id
  without existence-checking it (chat/chat-thread-resolution.ts); behavior
  for a stale/foreign id is undocumented — decide and document.
- Bounded live sessions for restored desks (#217 follow-on, research-backed):
  the persisted desk (context-tabs-store/context-desk-storage.ts) restores
  every open tab, and the document-session registry keeps a live
  websocket-subscribed Y.Doc per open tab — a 30-tab desk means 30 live
  sessions on every reload. Editor VIEWS are already bounded
  (ContextEditorMountHost MAX_MOUNTED_EDITORS=6, LRU); sessions are not.
  The move: lazy-connect background tabs' sessions on first view (same
  LRU shape as the view warm set), keeping only active/recent tabs live.
  Prior art: Yjs FAQ warns against hydrating many Y.Docs; research brief
  work/writer-ux/research/wss-localfirst-research-brief.md §4 (docs repo).
